President Obama has signed an emergency declaration for the State of South Carolina in response to the conditions caused by Hurricane Matthew. This declaration allows federal aid to supplement state, tribal, and local response efforts. The Department of Homeland Security, through FEMA, will coordinate disaster relief efforts to alleviate the hardship and suffering caused by the emergency. FEMA is authorized to mobilize equipment and resources to mitigate the impacts of the emergency. Emergency protective measures will be provided at 75 percent federal funding. W. Michael Moore has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area.